President Donald Trump issued a proclamation on National Agriculture Day, paying tribute to the strength of America's agricultural producers and their contribution to feeding the country and the world. He highlighted the increased productivity of US agriculture over the past century, thanks to innovations that have made American food safe, healthy, and affordable. The President also mentioned his efforts to negotiate better trade deals for the agricultural community, including the United States-Japan Trade Agreement and the United States-Mexico-Canada Agreement. He emphasized the importance of farming families and communities in the national economic supply chain and declared March 24, 2020, as National Agriculture Day.